# uv Workspace Monorepo

Multi-package Python monorepo powered by [uv workspaces](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/concepts/projects/workspaces/) —
one lockfile, one virtual environment, and shared tooling, with libraries under
`packages/` and deployable apps under `apps/`.

> Scaffolded with [create-awesome-python-app](https://github.com/Create-Python-App/create-python-app).
> **DON'T USE THIS REPO AS IS!** Generate your own and pick your options in the
> interactive menu. Check the docs for more information!

## Features

- 📦 **uv workspace** — one lockfile and one `.venv` for every member ([uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/))
- 🧱 **apps/ + packages/ split** — deployable apps consume shared libraries
- 🔗 **Local source wiring** — members depend on each other via `{ workspace = true }`
- 🦾 **Typed by default** — every member ships `py.typed`, checked with Pyright **and** mypy
- 🎯 **Shared tooling** — Ruff, Pyright, mypy, and pytest configured once at the root
- 🚀 **Independent releases** — build and publish each member on its own version

## Architecture

This template follows a monorepo layout inspired by turborepo's `apps/` + `packages/`
split, adapted to Python with a uv workspace. Code is organized around deployable
units and the shared libraries they consume, making it:

- 📦 **Modular** — each member is a self-contained distribution with its own `pyproject.toml`
- 🔄 **Maintainable** — edits to a library are visible to consumers immediately, no publish step
- 🚀 **Scalable** — new members are globbed in automatically (`packages/*`, `apps/*`)
- 🎨 **Clear** — the directory structure reflects what ships versus what is shared

For detailed information about the architecture, see [Project Structure](./docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md).

