## Pre-packed

### Dev tools

- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) — package manager, workspace, and virtual environment
- [Ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/) — fast linter and formatter
- [Pyright](https://microsoft.github.io/pyright/) — static type checker
- [mypy](https://mypy.readthedocs.io/) — static type checker (typed-by-default policy)
- [pytest](https://docs.pytest.org/) — test runner across all members
- [pre-commit](https://pre-commit.com/) — Git hooks to keep the tree clean
- [hatchling](https://hatch.pypa.io/latest/) — build backend for each member

### Members

- **`packages/core`** — an example shared library (`src/` layout, `py.typed`, tests).
- **`apps/cli`** — a [Typer](https://typer.tiangolo.com/) CLI that consumes `core`
  through the workspace, with a console script and a `python -m cli_app` entrypoint.

## Quickstart

You need [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) and Python 3.12+.

```bash
uv sync                          # install every workspace member into one .venv
uv run {{ commandName }} hello   # run the CLI app (apps/cli)
uv run pytest                    # test all members
```

## Development

While developing, you will rely mostly on `uv run` and the `make` shortcuts.
Run these from the workspace root:

| Command | `make` | Description |
| ------- | ------ | ----------- |
| `uv sync` | `make sync` | Install/relink every member into a single `.venv` |
| `uv run {{ commandName }} hello [NAME]` | — | Run the CLI app (`apps/cli`) |
| `uv run pytest` | `make test` | Run the whole test suite |
| `uv run ruff check .` | `make lint` | Lint every member |
| `uv run ruff format .` | `make format` | Format the workspace |
| `uv run pyright && uv run mypy` | `make typecheck` | Type-check every member |
| — | `make check` | Lint + typecheck + test |

## Production

Scripts for building and publishing individual members:

| Command | `make` | Description |
| ------- | ------ | ----------- |
| `uv build --all-packages` | `make build` | Build wheels/sdists for every member |
| `uv build --package {{ packagePrefix }}-core` | — | Build a single member |
| `uv publish --package {{ packagePrefix }}-core` | — | Publish a single member to an index |

See [docs/RELEASING.md](./docs/RELEASING.md) for the full versioning and publishing flow.

## Add a member

- **Library** → create `packages/<name>/` with a `pyproject.toml` and
  `src/<module>/`. It is picked up automatically by `packages/*`.
- **App** → create `apps/<name>/` the same way; it is picked up by `apps/*`.
- **Depend on a local library** → add its distribution name to the consumer's
  `dependencies` and mark it as a workspace source:

  ```toml
  [tool.uv.sources]
  "{{ packagePrefix }}-core" = { workspace = true }
  ```

See [docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md](./docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md) and
[docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md](./docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md) for details.

